  • Method Details

    • add

      void add​(int r, int c, int digit)
      Puts digit in the box row, col.
      Parameters:
      r - The row
      c - The column
      digit - The digit to insert in box row, col
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if row, col or digit is outside the range [0..9]

    • get

      int get​(int r, int c)
      Returns the number in box r,c. If the box i empty 0 is returned.
      Parameters:
      r - The row
      c - The column
      Returns:
      the number in box r,c or 0 if the box is empty.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if r or c is outside [0..9]

    • remove

      void remove​(int r, int c)
      Empties the provided box by setting the value to zero
      Parameters:
      r - Row of box
      c - Column of box
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if r or c is outside [0..9]

    • isValid

      boolean isValid()
      Checks that all filled in digits follows the the sudoku rules.
      Returns:
      true if postions are valid

    • solve

      boolean solve()
      Attempts to solve the sudoku recursively
      Returns:
      true if sudoku was solved

    • clear

      void clear()
      Empties all boxes by setting them to zero

    • getMatrix

      int[][] getMatrix()
      Returns the numbers in the sudoku. An empty box i represented by the value 0.
      Returns:
      the numbers in the grid

    • setMatrix

      void setMatrix​(int[][] m)
      Fills the grid with the digits in m. The digit 0 represents an empty box.
      Parameters:
      m - the matrix with the digits to insert
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if m has the wrong dimension or contains values outside the range [0..9]
